Helper functions to format rcells for various display

Helper functions to format rcells for various display

print_np(x)

Arguments

x

list produced by calc_rate/calc_diffor function
y

name of element to display
z

colspan for the cell

Examples


a_rate <- calc_rate(LETTERS[sample(1:3, 20, replace=T)], value = "A")
b_rate <- calc_rate(LETTERS[sample(1:3, 20, replace=T)], value = "A")
diffor <- calc_diffor(b_rate, a_rate)

print_np(a_rate)
#> [1] 7.00 0.35
#> attr(,"colspan")
#> [1] 1
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "rcell"
print_ci(a_rate, "ci", 2)
#> [1] 15.39092 59.21885
#> attr(,"conf.level")
#> [1] 0.95
#> attr(,"format")
#> [1] "(xx.xx, xx.xx)"
#> attr(,"colspan")
#> [1] 2
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "rcell"
print_ci(diffor, "diffci", 2)
#> [1] -24.96566  34.96566
#> attr(,"conf.level")
#> [1] 0.95
#> attr(,"format")
#> [1] "(xx.xx, xx.xx)"
#> attr(,"colspan")
#> [1] 2
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "rcell"
print_diffor(diffor, "diff", 1)
#> prop 1 
#>      5 
#> attr(,"format")
#> [1] "xx.xx"
#> attr(,"colspan")
#> [1] 1
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "rcell"
print_diffor(diffor, "or", 1)
#> [1] 1.238095
#> attr(,"format")
#> [1] "xx.xx"
#> attr(,"colspan")
#> [1] 1
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "rcell"
